		<div id="comment_body_64829451">They're not rolling a D20, dude. Know how much work you can get done in a day and do an estimate. It's either enough or it isn't so keep working or leave accordingly. I know they're not all sales commission jobs and factors can be outside your control but here's a little secret:<br>
If your department at the company isn't profitable and expenses don't scale with income, some of you are getting fired or passed up for raises anyway. So might as well get bonuses based on performance.</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64829451">

